  ' ============================================================
  ' ARCHETYPE SCHEMA
  ' ============================================================

  class ArchetypeSchema {
    +getId(): UUID
    +getUri(): URI
  }

  note top of ArchetypeSchema
    Defines the structure and semantics of systemic primitive archetypes,
    their instances and qualifiers, using archetype schemas.

    This enables extensible systemic definitions, data validations, and
    exploitation.

    **Rules**:
    - "id" MUST be unique among all systemic primitive instances (=> UUIDv6).
    - "uri" MUST be unique among all archetype schemas.

    **Generic schemas definitions**:
    - *Actuation Control Event Schemas*:
      define the generic structure of events whose meaning is: execute a
      specific actuation.

      name: CreationActuationControlEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "create"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: ModificationActuationControlEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "modify"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: DeletionActuationControlEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "delete"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode

      name: AcquisitionActuationControlEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "acquire"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode

    - *Actuation Event Schemas*:
      define the generic structure of events whose meaning is: specific
      actuation executed.

      name: CreationActuationEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "create"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: ModificationActuationEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "modify"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: DeletionActuationEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "delete"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode

      name: AcquisitionActuationEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "acquire"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode

    - *Actuation Feedback Event Schemas*:
      define the generic structure of events whose meaning is: specific
      actuation execution observed.

      name: CreationActuationFeedbackEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "create"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: ModificationActuationFeedbackEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "modify"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode
        - valueMapping: Map

      name: DeletionActuationFeedbackEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "delete"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode

      name: AcquisitionActuationFeedbackEventSchema
      properties:
        - operation: "acquire"
        - objectArchetypeName: String
        - criteria: LogicalOperatorNode
  end note

  ' ============================================================
  ' SYSTEMIC PRIMITIVE
  ' ============================================================

  abstract class SystemicPrimitive {
    +getId(): UUID
    +getName(): String
    +getArchetype(): SystemicPrimitiveArchetype
    +getQualifierArchetypes(): SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype[]
    +getQualifiers(): SystemicPrimitiveQualifier[]
  }

  note top of SystemicPrimitive
    A systemic primitive represents a systemics "second-order dynamics" concept
    of a system definition.

    **Rules**
    - The systemic primitive MUST conform to the structure and semantics
      defined in its schema (or vice-versa) held by its archetype.
    - "id" MUST be unique among all systemic primitive instances (=> UUIDv6).
    - "name" MUST be maximum 255 characters long.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive "0..*" o--> "1" SystemicPrimitiveArchetype : has
  SystemicPrimitive "1" *--> "0..*" SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype : has
  SystemicPrimitive "1" *--> "0..*" SystemicPrimitiveQualifier : has

  class SystemicPrimitiveArchetype {
    +getId(): UUID
    +getName(): String
    +getSchema(): ArchetypeSchema
    +getQualifierArchetypes(): SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype[]
  }

  note top of SystemicPrimitiveArchetype
    Defines the structure and semantics of a systemic primitive that can be
    instantiated.

    **Rules**
    - "id" MUST be unique among all systemic primitive instances (=> UUIDv6).
    - "name" MUST match the name of the schema.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all systemic primitive archetypes.
    - "name" MUST be maximum 255 characters long.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitiveArchetype "1" *--> "1" ArchetypeSchema : has
  SystemicPrimitiveArchetype "1" *--> "0..*" SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype : has

  class SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype {
    +getSchema(): ArchetypeSchema
    +getSystemicPrimitiveArchetype(): SystemicPrimitiveArchetype
  }

  note top of SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype
    Defines the structure and semantics of a qualifier that can be applied to
    all instances of a systemic primitive.

    This enables extensible semantic metadata associated to systemic primitives,
    enabling systemic exploitations of specific domain data.

    **Rules**
    - "name" MUST match the name of the schema.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all qualifier archetypes of this systemic
      primitive's archetype, and among all qualifier archetypes of systemic
      primitives instances of this archetype.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitiveArchetype <|-- SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype : is
  SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype "1" *--> "1" ArchetypeSchema : has
  SystemicPrimitiveArchetypeQualifierArchetype "1" o--> "1" SystemicPrimitiveArchetype : belongsTo

  class SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype {
    +getSchema(): ArchetypeSchema
    +getSystemicPrimitive(): SystemicPrimitive
  }

  note top of SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype
    Defines the structure and semantics of a qualifier that can be applied to
    a systemic primitive instance specifically.

    This enables extensible semantic metadata associated to systemic primitives,
    enabling systemic exploitations of specific domain data.

    **Rules**
    - "name" MUST match the name of the schema.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all qualifier archetypes of the systemic
      primitive instances having the same archetype as this instance, and among
      all qualifier archetypes of this systemic primitive archetype.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype : is
  SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype "1" *--> "1" ArchetypeSchema : has
  SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype "1" o--> "1" SystemicPrimitive : belongsTo

  class SystemicPrimitiveQualifier {
    +getArchetype(): SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype
    +getValue(): String
  }

  note top of SystemicPrimitiveQualifier
    A qualifier applied to a systemic primitive instance, providing
    additional semantic metadata about the primitive.

    **Rules**
    - The qualifier's value is formatted as JSON. It MUST conform to the
      structure, semantics, types, defined in its archetype's schema.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- SystemicPrimitiveQualifier : is
  SystemicPrimitiveQualifier "1" *--> "1" SystemicPrimitiveQualifierArchetype : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' SYSTEM
  ' ============================================================

  class System {
    +getType(): String
    +getRole(): String
    +getPurpose(): String
    +getPrinciples(): Principle[]
    +getCapacities(): Capacity[]
    +getInterfaces(): Interface[]
    +getSubSystems(): System[]
    +getPersistenceConditions(): Condition[]
    +getStateObjectArchetypes(): StateObjectArchetype[]

    +getGovernors(): Governor[]
    +getRegulators(): Regulator[]
    +getPolicies(): Policy[]
    +getRules(): Rule[]

    +getChannels(): Channel[]

    +getWorkflows(): Workflow[]
    +getFunctions(): Function[]
    +getDomainProperties(): PropertyReference[]

    +getMechanisms(): Mechanism[]
    +getReceptors(): Receptor[]
    +getEffectors(): Effector[]
    +getReactions(): Reaction[]
    +getInteractions(): Interaction[]
    +getPreconditions(): Condition[]
    +getPostconditions(): Condition[]
    +getInvariants(): Condition[]
    +getEventArchetypes(): EventArchetype[]
    +getBehavioralProperties(): BehavioralPropertyReference[]
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- System : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' CAPACITY
  ' ============================================================

  class Capacity {
    +getDescription(): String
    +getWorkflows(): Workflow[]
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Capacity : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' INTERFACE
  ' ============================================================

  class Interface {
    +getReceptors(): Receptor[]
    +getEffectors(): Effector[]
    +getChannels(): Channel[]
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Interface : is

  class ExternalInterface
  Interface <|-- ExternalInterface : is

  class InternalInterface
  Interface <|-- InternalInterface : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' CHANNEL
  ' ============================================================

  class Channel {
    +getProtocol(): String
    +getInteractions(): Interaction[]
    +getExternalSystemInterface(): Interface
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Channel : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' WORKFLOW
  ' ============================================================

  class Workflow {
    +getPurpose(): String
    +getFunctionsSequence(): Function[]
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Workflow : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' FUNCTION
  ' ============================================================

  class Function {
    +getPurpose(): String
    +getMechanism(): Mechanism
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Function : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' RECEPTOR
  ' ============================================================

  class Receptor {
    +getName(): String
    +getReceivedEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
  }

  note top of Receptor
    A receptor represents a mechanism's capability to receive events produced by
    mechanism's effectors. Such received event represent a cause for the
    mechanism to operate.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A receptor name MUST be unique among all receptors of the same system.
    - A receptor MUST be bound to exactly one event archetype.
    - If the bound event archetype is deleted, the receptor MUST be deleted.
    - If the receptor is deleted, the bound event archetype MUST NOT be deleted.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Receptor : is
  Receptor "1" o--> "1" EventArchetype : on

  ' ============================================================
  ' EFFECTOR
  ' ============================================================

  class Effector {
    +getName(): String
    +getProducedEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
    +getProducedEventMapping(): EffectorEventMapping
  }

  note top of Effector
    An effector represents a mechanism's capability to produce events. Such
    produced events represent the effect of a mechanism's operation on the
    system.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - An effector name MUST be unique among all effectors of the same system.
    - An effector MUST be bound to exactly one event archetype.
    - An event archetype MUST be bound to exactly one effector.
    - If the bound event archetype is deleted, its effector MUST be deleted.
    - If the effector is deleted, the bound event archetype MUST be deleted.
    - An effector MUST have exactly one event mapping defining how the produced
      event instance is constructed from source receptor's events.
    - If the effector is deleted, its event mapping MUST be deleted.
    - The event mapping MUST NOT be deleted without its effector being deleted.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Effector : is
  Effector "1" *--> "1" EventArchetype : on
  Effector "1" *--> "1" EffectorEventMapping : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' EFFECTOR EVENT MAPPING
  ' ============================================================

  class EffectorEventMapping {
    +getTargetEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
    +getSourceEventArchetypes(): EventArchetype[]
    +getEventPropertyMappings(): EffectorEventPropertyMapping[]
  }

  note top of EffectorEventMapping
    Captures, at design time, how an effector's produced event instance is
    constructed from one or more source events.

    This enables end-to-end data transformation traceability.

    **Event Mapping Rules**
    - For each effector event mapping M:
      - Ensure M.targetEventArchetype == effector.on (target event archetype).
    - Ensure a receptor exists for each M.sourceEventArchetype.
    - Ensure a control sequence exists for each distinct M.sourceEventArchetype,
      with triggering event == M.sourceEventArchetype.
    - Ensure a control exists in that sequence which selects the effector.
    - When multiple controls exist in a sequence, order deterministically
      (e.g. by effector name) to keep regeneration idempotent.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A mapping MUST reference exactly one target event archetype (the one
      bound to the effector).
    - A mapping MUST reference zero or more source event archetypes.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- EffectorEventMapping : is
  EffectorEventMapping "1" o--> "1" EventArchetype : mapsTo
  EffectorEventMapping "1" o--> "0..*" EventArchetype : mapsFrom
  EffectorEventMapping "1" *--> "1..*" EffectorEventPropertyMapping : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' EFFECTOR EVENT PROPERTY MAPPING
  ' ============================================================

  class EffectorEventPropertyMapping {
    +getTargetPath(): String
    +getSourcePath(): String
  }

  note top of EffectorEventPropertyMapping
    Defines how a specific property of the target event is set and derived from
    source events.

    This enables end-to-end data transformation traceability, at property level.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - The target and source pathes MUST reference a valid property in the target
      and source event archetype schema.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- EffectorEventPropertyMapping : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' INTERACTION
  ' ============================================================

  class Interaction {
    +getEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Interaction : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  abstract class Mechanism {
    +getName(): String
    +getReceptors(): Receptor[]
    +getEffectors(): Effector[]
  }

  note top of Mechanism
    A mechanism represents a system's capability to process input events
    received via its receptors, and produce output events via its effectors.

    A mechanism represents an atomic causal unit of behavior within a system.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A mechanism name MUST be unique among all mechanisms of the same system.
    - A mechanism MUST have at least one receptor and one effector.
    - If a mechanism is deleted, its receptors and effectors MUST be
      deleted.
    - If a receptor or effector is deleted, the mechanism MUST NOT be deleted,
      except if the receptor or effector is the last one the mechanism owns.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Mechanism : is
  Mechanism "1" *--> "1..*" Receptor : has
  Mechanism "1" *--> "1..*" Effector : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' GOVERNOR MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  class GovernorMechanism {
    +getPolicies(): Policy[]
  }

  note top of GovernorMechanism
    A governor mechanism establishes high-level policies that guide the overall
    behavior of the system it governs, via supervisor mechanisms receiving
    these policy events and operationalizing these policies as rules.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A governor mechanism MUST own at least one policy.
    - Policies associated with a governor mechanism MUST be unique within the
      context of that mechanism.
  end note

  ControllerMechanism <|-- GovernorMechanism : is
  GovernorMechanism "1" *--> "0..*" Policy : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' SUPERVISOR MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  class SupervisorMechanism {
    +getRules(): Rule[]
  }

  note top of SupervisorMechanism
    A supervisor mechanism oversees the operation of other mechanisms within
    the system, ensuring they adhere to defined rules and policies.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A supervisor mechanism MUST receive at least one governor event.
    - A supervisor mechanism MUST have at least one associated rule.
    - Rules associated with a supervisor mechanism MUST be unique within the
      context of that mechanism.
  end note

  ControllerMechanism <|-- SupervisorMechanism : is
  SupervisorMechanism "1" *--> "0..*" Rule : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' CONTROLLER MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  class ControllerMechanism {
    +getControlSequences(): ControlSequence[]
  }

  note top of ControllerMechanism
    A controller mechanism is a control mechanism. It conditionnally produces
    effectors (output events) based on events received via its receptors.

    **Todo**:
    - Implement join/fork of control sequences (which may define parallel
      execution).

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A controller mechanism MUST own at least one control sequence.
    - Control sequences associated with a controller mechanism MUST be unique
      within the context of the system.
    - If a controller mechanism is deleted, its control sequences MUST be
      deleted, and vice-versa IF it is the last control sequence the mechanism
      owns.
  end note

  Mechanism <|-- ControllerMechanism : is
  ControllerMechanism "1" *--> "1..*" ControlSequence : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' ACTUATOR MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  class ActuatorMechanism {
    +getActuation(): Actuation
  }

  note top of ActuatorMechanism
    An actuator mechanism is an execution mechanism acting on a state object.

    **Auto Definition Rules**:
    - For every event archetype E whose schema is a subtype of
      ActuationControlEventSchema, the actuator mechanism MUST have (or derive)
      a receptor bound to E.
    - For every receptor bound to E, the actuator mechanism MUST have an
      effector bound to event O whose schema is subtype of ActuationEventSchema.
    - For every effector bound to O, the actuator mechanism MUST have an
      actuation representing the action performed on the state object.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - An actuator mechanism MUST own exactly one actuation.
    - Actuations associated with an actuator mechanism MUST be unique
      within the context of the system.
    - If an actuator mechanism is deleted, its actuation MUST be deleted,
      and vice-versa.
  end note

  Mechanism <|-- ActuatorMechanism : is
  ActuatorMechanism "1" *--> "1" Actuation : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' SENSOR MECHANISM
  ' ============================================================

  class SensorMechanism {
    +getSensing(): Sensing
  }

  note top of SensorMechanism
    A sensor mechanism is an observation mechanism on actuations.

    **Auto Definition Rules**:
    - For every event archetype E whose schema is a subtype of
      ActuationEventSchema, the sensor mechanism MUST have (or derive) a
      receptor bound to E.
    - For every receptor bound to E, the sensor mechanism MUST have an
      effector bound to event O whose schema is subtype of
      ActuationFeedbackEventSchema.
    - For every effector bound to O, the sensor mechanism MUST have a
      sensing representing the observation of the actuation.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A sensor mechanism MUST own exactly one sensing.
    - Sensing associated with a sensor mechanism MUST be unique within the
      context of the system.
  end note

  Mechanism <|-- SensorMechanism : is
  SensorMechanism "1" *--> "1" Sensing : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' CONTROL SEQUENCE
  ' ============================================================
  
  class ControlSequence {
    +getTriggeringEvent(): EventArchetype
    +getConditions(): LogicalOperatorNode
    +getIterationConditions(): LogicalOperatorNode
    +getControls(): Control[]
  }

  note top of ControlSequence
    A control sequence represents a series of controls that are executed in
    response to a specific triggering event.

    A control sequence may be iterated while its iteration conditions hold.

    **Validation Rules**:
    - The conditions operands referencing event properties MUST exist in the
      corresponding event archetype schemas beared by the mechanism receptor.
    - The conditions operands representing a literal value MUST be validated
      against the corresponding event archetype schema beared by the mechanism
      receptor.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A control sequence MUST be triggered by exactly one event archetype.
    - A control sequence MUST have at least one control.
    - If a control sequence is deleted, its controls MUST be deleted, and
      vice-versa IF it is the last control the sequence owns.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- ControlSequence : is
  ControlSequence "1" o--> "1" EventArchetype : on
  ControlSequence "1" *--> "1..*" Control : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' CONTROL
  ' ============================================================

  class Control {
    +getName(): String
    +getConditions(): LogicalOperatorNode
    +getIterationConditions(): LogicalOperatorNode
    +getEffector(): Effector
  }

  note top of Control
    A control consists to map data to its effector's event.

    **Auto Definition Rules**:
    - When a control is added to a control sequence, required source event
      archetypes SHOULD be inferred from the selected effector's mapping.
    - If the enclosing mechanism does not yet have receptors for those source
      archetypes, the application SHOULD propose creating them.
    - If the required source archetype does not match the control sequence's
      triggering event, the application SHOULD propose creating a new control
      sequence triggered by that source archetype (chained sequences).

    **Validation Rules**:
    - The conditions operands referencing event properties MUST exist in the
      corresponding event archetype schemas beared by the mechanism receptor.
    - The conditions operands representing a literal value MUST be validated
      against the corresponding event archetype schema beared by the mechanism
      receptor.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - A control name MUST be unique among all controls of the system.
    - A control MUST have exactly one effector.
    - If a control is deleted, its effector MUST be deleted, and vice-versa.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Control : is
  Control "1" *--> "1" Effector : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' ACTUATION
  ' ============================================================

  class Actuation {
    +getName(): String
  }

  note top of Actuation
    An actuation represents a mechanism's capability to perform actions on a
    state object of the system.

    Actuation actuate either *first-order dynamics* objects (functional) or
    *second-order dynamics* objects (system, interface, policy, rule, control,
    actuation, etc).

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - The actuation name MUST be unique among all actuations of the same system.
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Actuation : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' SENSING (checkpoint)
  ' ============================================================

  class Sensing {
    +getName(): String
  }
  SystemicPrimitive <|-- Sensing : is

  ' ============================================================
  ' EVENT ARCHETYPE
  ' ============================================================

  class EventArchetype {
    +getName(): String
    +getSchema(): ArchetypeSchema
  }

  note top of EventArchetype
    Defines the structure and semantics of an event that can be emitted or
    received by a system via its effectors and receptors.

    This enables extensible event definitions, data validations, and
    exploitations.

    **Rules**
    - "name" MUST match the name of the schema.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all entities classified as "archetype".
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- EventArchetype : is
  EventArchetype "0..*" o--> "1" ArchetypeSchema : has
  
  ' ============================================================
  ' STATE OBJECT ARCHETYPE
  ' ============================================================

  class StateObjectArchetype {
    +getName(): String
    +getSchema(): ArchetypeSchema
  }

  note top of StateObjectArchetype
    Defines the structure and semantics of a state object that can be used to
    represent the state of a system.

    This enables extensible state object definitions, data validations, and
    exploitations.

    **Rules**
    - "name" MUST match the name of the schema.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all entities classified as "archetype".
  end note

  SystemicPrimitive <|-- StateObjectArchetype : is
  StateObjectArchetype "1" *--> "1" ArchetypeSchema : has

  ' ============================================================
  ' CONSTRAINT
  ' ============================================================

  abstract class Constraint {
    +getId(): UUID
    +getStatus(): Enum <<ConstraintStatusEnum>>
  }

  enum ConstraintStatusEnum {
    "proposed"
    "active"
    "deprecated"
    "retired"
  }

  class Principle {
    +getStatement(): String
  }

  class Policy {
    +getStatement(): String
  }

  class Rule {
    +getStatement(): String
  }

